-- 
2011-09-08T15:07:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-08/cyprus-posts-4-3-budget-deficit-in-first-seven-months-of-year.html
Cyprusâ€™s budget deficit widened in
the first 7 months of 2011 to 4.3 percent of the economy from
2.7 percent the year before on increased spending and falling
revenue, the  ministry of finance  said.  The fiscal deficit on a cash basis in January to July was
793.5 million euros ($1.1 billion), the ministry said in a
statement on its website today.  Public spending in January to July rose 6.2 percent to more
than 4.2 billion euros, while public revenue fell 2 percent
below 3.5 billion euros, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
